From cedcb83034ff819bbf97baf55381aedcd52dfdd1 Mon Jun 8 11:14:00 2026 +0100 
From: "Enrico Weigelt, metux IT consult" <info@metux.net>
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 10:52:49 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] os: osdep.h: fix FTBS on musl

https://github.com/X11Libre/xserver/issues/2890

musl doesn't indirectly include errno.h as much as other libc's do.
In general it's a good idea to always explicitly include what's needed,
instead of relying on indirect includes.

Signed-off-by: Enrico Weigelt, metux IT consult <info@metux.net>
---
 os/osdep.h | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/os/osdep.h b/os/osdep.h
index a430555a8a..443dd477e1 100644
--- a/os/osdep.h
+++ b/os/osdep.h
@@ -50,6 +50,7 @@ SOFTWARE.
 
 #include <X11/Xdefs.h>
 
+#include <errno.h>
 #include <limits.h>
 #include <signal.h>
 #include <stddef.h>

